{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0eccaf12-68cc-41f9-b9d1-67a2d46f5ae3","content":"Here are the issues I found:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** — Required field for .NET templates is absent.\n2. **`defaultValue` not in `choices`** (line 10) — `targetFramework` defaults to `\"net7.0\"`, but only `\"net8.0\"` and `\"net9.0\"` are valid choices.\n3. **`choices` format is wrong** (lines 11-14) — Should be an array of objects (`[{\"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \"...\"}]`), not a dictionary.\n4. **Invalid int default** (line 24) — `maxRetries` is `datatype: \"int\"` but `defaultValue` is `\"abc\"`.\n5. **Bool default non-standard** (line 19) — `enableLogging` uses `\"yes\"` instead of `\"true\"`.\n6. **`computed1` missing `value`** (line 27) — Computed symbols require a `value` expression.\n7. **`generated1` missing `generator`** (line 30) — Generated symbols require a `generator` property.\n8. **`postActions` missing `actionId`** (line 34) — Each post action needs an `actionId`.\n9. **`shortName: \"restore\"`** conflicts with the built-in `dotnet restore` command.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eb77cb3c-4b95-4706-bc49-164075481e44","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze this template.json for issues. This appears to be a .NET template configuration file. Let me check for problems:\n\n1. **Missing `identity`** - The `identity` field is required in .NET templates but is missing here.\n\n2. **`defaultValue` not in `choices`** (line 10) - `targetFramework` has `defaultValue: \"net7.0\"` but the choices only include `\"net8.0\"` and `\"net9.0\"`. So the default value doesn't match any valid choice.\n\n3. **`defaultValue` type mismatch for `maxRetries`** (line 24) - `maxRetries` has `datatype: \"int\"` but `defaultValue: \"abc\"` which is not a valid integer.\n\n\n4. **`enableLogging` defaultValue** (line 19) - The boolean field has `defaultValue: \"yes\"` when it should use `\"true\"` or `\"false\"` for proper .NET template compatibility.\n\n5. **`computed1` missing `value`** (lines 27-28) - Computed symbols need a `value` property with an expression.\n\n6. **`generated1` missing `generator`** (lines 29-31) - Generated symbols require a `generator` property to specify how to generate the value.\n\n7. **`postActions` entry missing `actionId`** (lines 33-36) - Post-action entries need an `actionId` field to identify what action to perform.\n\n8. **`choices` format** - The `targetFramework` choices are structured as an object, but the .NET template engine expects an array of objects where each item has `choice` and `description` properties. The correct format should be an array like `[{\"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \".NET 8\"}]` rather than the object/dictionary format shown here.\n\nI'm also noticing that `shortName: \"restore\"` might conflict with the built-in `dotnet restore` command, which could cause issues. Let me compile the full list of problems I've identified.","outputTokens":920,"requestId":"C814:285BD2:6D8C466:75D61B2:6A03CCF2"},"id":"a8284b39-a2c2-4fb0-80c7-ee97819a1d93","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:59:46.221Z","parentId":"5dd3f8b7-0126-4fd7-8f7a-876385251e5c"}
